2011off\u201d attitude of A or the hostility of B and D, making C the more balanced choice for safety\u2011critical, long\u2011haul flights.\n- **Remaining uncertainty:** How much C\u2019s difficulty communicating ideas and egocentric attitude will actually affect real\u2011world cockpit interaction and decision\u2011making on extended missions.\n- **What would change my vote:** Concrete evidence that Candidate\u202fA\u2019s \u201cshow\u2011off\u201d behavior and resistance to new ideas have not led to any crew\u2011resource\u2011management incidents, or that Candidate\u202fC\u2019s communication issues have resulted in safety\u2011critical misunderstandings, would shift the balance toward A (or away from C).\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
